OL,3,COnline Safety Act 'missing vital
OL,4,Copportunity' on suicide content
OL,6,F"We know the Secretary of State has
OL,7,Fchosen to accept Ofcom's advice, so
OL,8,Fbasically, this means dangerous
OL,9,Fsuicide and self-harm content is going
OL,10,Fto continue to be accessible to anyone
OL,11,Fover the age of 18.
OL,13,F"Turning 18 doesn't make you any less
OL,14,Fvulnerable to this content. Lots of
OL,15,Fresearch shows the part that the
OL,16,Finternet has played in suicides."
